Jay Han (jayhan@cs.washington.edu) writes:

> I need to get hold of sources for RSA cryptography (which basically
> means code for computing A^E (mod M) at a decent speed).  I'd prefer C
> sources, but I can convert from any common language (except Prolog :-).
> Also, are there any sources to random prime number generators to go with
> it?

The PGP, RIPEM, and RSAREF packages contain all you are asking for.
The first can be found at soda.berkeley.edu and the other two on
rsa.com.

Regards,
Vesselin
